JVM is responsible for assigning default value to global/instance/class variables

Constructor in Java is a special type of method that is used to initialize the Object

Rules for creating a Java Constructor

   accessModifier nameOfTheClass(can/t parameters)
   {
      initialize the object only
   }
   Types of Constructors

   accessModifier  nameOfTheClass()
   {

   }

   accessModifier  nameOfTheClass(with parameters)
   {

   }

   We cannot call a constructor explicitly[on your own]